# TRIVY IGNORE FILE
# ------------------
# Every entry here is a deliberate, documented risk decision — not a blanket
# suppression. Each CVE is either (a) in OS packages this Flask app never
# invokes at runtime, or (b) blocked from a real fix by a dependency version
# constraint that's tracked and worth revisiting later. Nothing here is
# ignored just to make the scan pass.
#
# Review periodically: re-run `docker run --rm aquasec/trivy image <image>`
# without this file to see the current full list, and remove entries here
# once a real fix becomes available (Debian patches these on its own
# schedule; check Fixed Version column, currently blank for most below).

# --- util-linux family: libblkid partition-parsing integer overflow ---
# Affects bsdutils, libblkid1, libsmartcols1, libuuid1, util-linux.
# This app is a stateless Flask API in a container — it never parses disk
# partitions or block devices. No fix available yet upstream.
CVE-2026-53615

# --- gzip: buffer overflow in LZH decompression ---
# The app never invokes the gzip binary directly, and Python's own gzip
# module (used nowhere in this codebase) is unaffected — this CVE is
# specific to the standalone LZH decompression path in GNU gzip's CLI.
CVE-2026-41992

# --- libacl1: symlink traversal privilege escalation via ACL functions ---
# App never manipulates POSIX ACLs or extended file permissions.
CVE-2026-54369

# --- ncurses: buffer overflow (libncursesw6, libtinfo6, ncurses-base) ---
# This is a terminal UI library. The app runs headless behind gunicorn —
# no interactive terminal session ever touches this container.
CVE-2025-69720

# --- Perl runtime + Archive::Tar / IO::Compress modules ---
# perl-base is a Debian base-image dependency, not something this app uses.
# The Flask app and its Python dependencies never invoke Perl in any form.
# Grouped together since all five affect the same unused perl-base package.
CVE-2026-42496
CVE-2026-8376
CVE-2026-42497
CVE-2026-48962
CVE-2026-9538

# --- protobuf: DoS via recursion depth bypass ---
# UNLIKE the entries above, this one genuinely matters — protobuf is core
# to the google-cloud-* SDKs this app actually uses for Secret Manager and
# Cloud Logging. A fix exists (protobuf 5.29.6 / 6.33.5) but is BLOCKED:
# google-cloud-logging==3.11.0 pins protobuf to <5.0.0dev, so no patched
# version satisfies both dependencies simultaneously (confirmed via direct
# pip resolution attempt — see requirements.txt history). Accepted as a
# tracked risk. Revisit when google-cloud-logging releases a version
# supporting protobuf 5.x, then remove this line and re-pin protobuf.
CVE-2026-0994
